title: 14-yr-old Palestinian-American citizen killed by Israeli Forces in West Bank

description: In a significant act of goodwill in 2016, India gifted Sri Lanka 88 ambulances, which have since expanded to a fleet of 322. These ambulances provide crucial emergency services, saving approximately 1.5 million lives. India's gesture underscores the strong cooperative relations between the two nations, as seen in recent humanitarian efforts in Myanmar.
title: Ambulances gifted by India help Sri Lanka save 1.5 million lives
Brooklyn horror: Police shoot man after he stabs four girls at home
Fed Judge again orders Trump admin to return man wrongly deported to El Salvador

description: India will open a new naval base for nuclear submarines and warships in Andhra Pradesh next year. Upgrades to the Karwar base in Karnataka are also ongoing. The new and upgraded facilities aim to strengthen India's naval capabilities in the Indian Ocean Region, particularly in response to China's growing presence.
title: India plans to set up N-sub base in Andhra next year

description: Mariam Alexander Baby has been appointed as CPM's new general secretary during the 24th congress in Madurai. Baby, 71, is the second person from Kerala to hold this position, succeeding Sitaram Yechury. His appointment faced some opposition, but he secured broad support, including endorsements from key members.
title: Karats out of politburo, former Kerala minister Baby named CPM general secretary

description: The Supreme Court of India has issued a notice to an NRI woman for possibly contemptuous behavior. After agreeing to settle a matrimonial dispute, she sought a US court order to restrain SC from proceeding. The SC questions why contempt proceedings shouldn't be initiated.
title: NRI woman faces contempt for seeking US injunction against SC

description: West Bengal Governor CV Ananda Bose submitted his objections to CM Mamata Banerjee’s recommendations for vice-chancellors of 17 universities to the Supreme Court in a sealed cover. The Governor's reservations are based on background reviews and reports, which the SC was not aware of during the last hearing.
title: Bengal guv opposes Didi’s 17 VC picks, gives documents to SC

description: Congress is the only national political party that occupies two government bungalows in Lutyen's Delhi, while four other parties, including BJP, have one each. These bungalows have been allotted for party office use with the policy requiring vacation three years after office building completion or land allocation.
title: Congress now only party left with 2 Lutyen’s bungalows

description: Calcutta High Court clarified that consumer forums cannot issue arrest warrants like a criminal court, but can only order civil detention to enforce judgments. This arose from a case where an arrest warrant was wrongfully issued against a branch manager by the District Consumer Forum for an automobile payment dispute.
title: Consumer forums can issue detention orders, not arrest warrants: Calcutta HC

description: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat stated that all Indians, including Muslims, are welcome at shakhas if they respect the 'Bharat Mata ki Jai' slogan and the saffron flag. Bhagwat emphasized the importance of unity above religious differences and called for ending caste discrimination during his visit to Varanasi.
title: Muslims can be at shakha if they chant ‘Bharat Mata’: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat

description: Apple and Samsung are shifting their production to India to counter higher US tariffs on imports from China and Vietnam. This move aims to retain competitiveness in the US market, with Apple increasingly using Indian factories for iPhone shipments and Samsung also considering India as a temporary measure for its exports.
title: Trump's tariffs: Apple, Samsung to up dispatch of India-made stuff

description: Police in J&K have identified 7,200 mule accounts this year with estimates suggesting the total could reach 30,000. The accounts, used for laundering money via cyber fraud, involve transactions in crores. Nineteen arrests were made in Srinagar, and investigations are ongoing.
title: J&K police uncover 7,200 mule accounts tied to cybercrime, money laundering

description: Luka Doncic will play for the Los Angeles Lakers against the Oklahoma City Thunder on April 6, 2025. Doncic has been managing minor ankle soreness, but is fully available. The game marks the first matchup since Doncic was traded to the Lakers. The Lakers may limit minutes for key players to ensure full availability for Doncic’s return to Dallas.
title: LA Lakers vs OKC Thunder final injury report: Is Luka Doncic playing?

description: Uttar Pradesh police inaugurated a hi-tech police outpost opposite Shahi Jama Masjid in Sambhal, featuring a watch tower and CCTV control room. Built in 100 days, it includes inscriptions from sacred texts. The opening coincided with the reopening of a temple after 46 years.
title: Sambhal gets a thana made with bricks thrown by rioters

description: In the financial year 2024-25, the MGNREGA job scheme generated over 288 crore persondays of work, less than 2023-24 but still above pre-pandemic levels. Experts suggest that the reduced budget allocation may have played a role in controlling work demand despite signs of rural distress improvement.
title: Work generated under NREGS in ’24-25 less than ’23-24 numbers

description: A rift within the INDIA bloc emerged as newly elected CPM general secretary MA Baby criticized Congress for attacking Kerala CM Pinarayi Vijayan. Baby urged Rahul Gandhi to act responsibly, highlighting tensions in the alliance. Despite these issues, Baby expressed hope for overcoming differences and emphasized the need for unity to strengthen the CPI(M).
title: Another crack in INDIA bloc? CPM attacks Rahul for 'arrest Kerala CM' remarks

description: The Indian government is unlikely to relax investment restrictions on Chinese companies due to concerns over their opaque ownership and ties with the Chinese military. Despite private sector appeals, the government's vigilance is heightened by issues such as China's non-market economy practices and their impact on manufacturing ambitions in India.
title: Govt unlikely to ease checks on investments from China
How the Atlantic’s editor ended up in a Signal war chat with Trump officials

description: Sudarsan Pattnaik, a renowned sand sculptor from Odisha, received the first Fred Darrington award for his 10-feet sand sculpture of Lord Ganesha at SandWorld in Dorset, England. The sculpture promotes the message of 'World Peace.' The award commemorates 100 years since Darrington began professional sand sculptures on Weymouth beach.
title: Odisha sculptor wins first ever prize at international sand festival in Weymouth

description: Hindu devotees with saffron flags returning from a Ram Navami procession were allegedly attacked in Kolkata's Park Circus area, according to West Bengal BJP. Union minister Sukanta Majumdar criticized the police for their inaction, labeling it as targeted violence influenced by political motives.
title: BJP alleges Ram Navami violence in Kolkata, Police react

description: Gujarat Titans secured a seven-wicket victory over Sunrisers Hyderabad in the Indian Premier League on Sunday, led by Shubman Gill's unbeaten 61 and Mohammed Siraj's four-wicket haul. Gill and Washington Sundar's crucial partnership anchored the run-chase despite early dismissals, and Sherfane Rutherford finished the match with a quickfire 35 not out.
title: IPL: Class acts Gill, Siraj lead GT's big win over SRH

description: Ukrainian President Zelenskyy demands a rapid response from US President Trump as Russia refuses an unconditional ceasefire amid ongoing war. Zelenskyy cites increased Russian attacks, urging for greater pressure. French President Macron also calls for immediate action. Trump seeks a partial truce while Putin remains open to dialogue.
title: 'We are waiting': Zelenskyy slams US silence as Putin rejects ceasefire

description: 'Instant Scholar' is a Times of India initiative to make academic research accessible to a wider audience. If you are a Ph.D. scholar and would like to publish a summary of your research in this section, please share a summary and authorisation to publish it. For submission, and any question on this initiative, write to us at instantscholar@timesgroup.com
title: Instant scholar: How Noam Chomsky’s PhD thesis 'Transformational Analysis' reshaped linguistics

description: MS Dhoni, once renowned as Indian cricket's top 'finisher', is facing scrutiny in IPL 2025 after failing to deliver with the bat for three consecutive matches. Despite his sharp wicket-keeping skills, Dhoni's declining performance and strike rate are major concerns for the Chennai Super Kings, now at ninth place. Although Dhoni continues to be sharp behind the stumps, his strike rate has seen a significant dip — down to 138.18 from a remarkable 220.55 in the previous season. His inability to find boundaries consistently has been a cause of concern, especially in high-pressure chases.
title: 'MS Dhoni should have retired a long time ago'
Scorching April begins: IMD warns prolonged heatwave in Delhi, UP and Rajasthan

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad’s openers Abhishek Sharma and Travis Head faltered early in their IPL 2025 match against Gujarat Titans, with both falling to Mohammed Siraj. Despite a 50-run stand between Nitish Kumar Reddy and Heinrich Klaasen, Hyderabad struggled and ended with 152/8. Siraj's outstanding 4-17 helped restrict them, while Cummins and Shami added late runs.
title: Kavya Maran loses cool after Abhishek, Travis Head flop again for SRH
'Stalin insulted PM': Annamalai slams TN CM for skipping Rameswaram event

description: Microsoft's 50th anniversary event at its Redmond headquarters faced disruption twice by Pro-Palestine supporters who are women employees. They criticized the company's alleged role in aiding violence in Gaza through its technology, demanding Microsoft to cut ties with Israel.
title: Who is Indian American Vaniya Agrawal who 'shamed' Microsoft CEOs

description: The Ministry of Statistics and Programme Implementation reports that women own 39.2% of all bank accounts in India, with a higher proportion in rural areas. The gender-specific publication highlights female participation in banking, stock markets, startups, and politics, while indicating steady progress in education and workforce involvement. This report underscores the need for gender-sensitive policies to promote inclusive development.
title: Women own 39.2% of bank accounts in India: Government report
Americans tell 'Elon and Felon' to take 'hands off' eggs, Canada and more

description: Ex-Finance Minister P Chidambaram challenges PM Modi's claim of increased funding to Tamil Nadu under NDA, explaining that economic metrics naturally rise over time. PM Modi states more funds allocated to the state, but DMK's MK Stalin criticizes the Center for neglecting Tamil Nadu's financial needs.
title: 'Any 1st yr student ...': Cong slams PM over TN funds remark; BJP hits back

description: Young spinner Digvesh Singh Rathi impresses in IPL 2025 with his performance and unique action resembling Sunil Narine. His economical bowling for Lucknow Super Giants earned him the Player of the Match award in a win over Mumbai Indians. Rishabh Pant helped Rathi meet his idol Narine in Kolkata. Emulating Narine, Rathi transformed his bowling style to prioritize accuracy and control, aiming to prevent boundaries and earn recognition for his disciplined approach.
title: Rishabh Pant fulfils Digvesh Rathi's long-awaited dream

description: Mohammed Siraj reached the milestone of 100 wickets in the IPL during Gujarat Titans vs. Sunrisers Hyderabad match in 2025, becoming the 26th bowler in IPL history to do so. He now has 100 wickets in 97 matches, with 42 taken in powerplay, emphasizing his new-ball impact. Yuzvendra Chahal, who is currently playing for Punjab Kings, tops the list with 206 wickets under his belt.
title: Rs 2 cr to Rs 12.25 cr star! Siraj hits 100-wicket mark in style

description: Starting April 7, the People's Union USA will lead a weeklong boycott of Walmart, targeting corporate greed and political corruption. This follows previous retail boycotts over DEI initiatives. Walmart, which withdrew its DEI programs, has reportedly been less affected than other retailers by these protests.
title: How Walmart Boycott is different from Boycott calls against Target and Amazon

description: AIADMK cast doubts over the veracity of Prime Minister Modi's welfare scheme claims in Tamil Nadu, alleging fake beneficiaries under DMK rule. This development adds to speculation about a potential BJP-AIADMK alliance ahead of the 2026 elections aimed at ousting DMK from power.
title: Amid tie-up talks, AIADMK pans PM Modi's 'tall claims' in Tamil Nadu

description: Mumbai Indians' head coach confirms that Jasprit Bumrah is fit and ready for selection in the upcoming IPL match against RCB. Bumrah's return is crucial as MI has only one victory so far.
title: Bumrah declared fit for MI, set to play against ...

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad suffer a setback as pacer Harshal Patel is hospitalized and misses the IPL 2025 match against Gujarat Titans. Jaydev Unadkat replaces him, while Gujarat Titans introduce Washington Sundar. Sunrisers' captain Pat Cummins focuses on aggressive play after winning the toss. Captain Pat Cummins confirmed at the toss that Harshal will miss the match, with Jaydev Unadkat replacing him in the playing XI.
title: Major blow for Sunrisers Hyderabad! Star pacer hospitalised

description: Amitabh Bachchan, Dharmendra, and other celebrities pay tribute to Manoj Kumar, while Jacqueline Fernandez mourns her mother's loss. Bobby Deol and Raghav Juyal reveal a new side in Aryan Khan's upcoming directorial venture, and Will Smith delights fans with a Bhangra performance alongside Diljit Dosanjh. Stay updated with the latest entertainment news and stories.
title: Top 5 news: Big B-Dharmendra pay tribute to Manoj Kumar

description: At the foot of Pakistan's impossibly high mountains whitened by frost all year round, farmers grappling with a lack of water have created their own ice towers. "The water must be propelled so that it freezes in the air when temperatures drop below zero, creating ice towers," said Zakir Hussain Zakir, a professor at the University of Baltistan.
title: Artificial glaciers boost water supply in northern Pakistan

description: Team India secured victories in the 2024 T20 World Cup and the 2025 ICC Champions Trophy under Rohit Sharma's leadership. With Rohit's future uncertain, Kapil Dev supports Hardik Pandya as the new white-ball captain, citing his youth and team-building potential for upcoming ICC events. Hardik Pandya is currently active only in white-ball formats for India, having last played a Test match over six years ago.
title: Not Rohit, not Suryakumar! Kapil Dev reveals who should captain Team India
Watch: First train crosses new Pamban Bridge after PM flags off sea link

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi criticized Tamil Nadu leaders for not signing letters in Tamil during a public address. He also urged the state to offer medical courses in Tamil to help underprivileged students. This comes amid tensions over the National Education Policy and language imposition concerns.
title: 'At least sign in Tamil': PM Modi takes shot at DMK govt amid language row

description: Flight Lieutenant Siddharth Yadav, a 28-year-old Indian Air Force fighter pilot, was laid to rest with full military honours in his native village after a Jaguar jet crash near Jamnagar. Grieving family and villagers attended the ceremony, which included a gun salute. An inquiry has been launched into the accident.
title: 'Baby, you didn't come to take me': Fiance's heartbreaking cry at IAF pilot's funeral

description: Farmer leader Jagjit Singh Dallewal ended his 131-day fast at a Kisan mahapanchayat in Fatehgarh Sahib, citing increased demands to mobilize farmers nationwide. Despite remaining skeptical of government promises, he vowed to continue the struggle for minimum support price on crops and participate in upcoming meetings with ministers. Dallewal plans to lead future protests as needed.
title: Farmers' protest: Dallewal ends 131-day fast, to 'fight again, at right time'

description: Union Minister Piyush Goyal urged Indian startups to focus on high-tech sectors like semiconductors and AI instead of convenience-driven ventures. Harsh Goenka and other industry leaders supported this view, emphasizing the need for a mindset shift to enhance India's global competitiveness.
title: Harsh Goenka on why ‘uproar’ over union minister Piyush Goyal & Narayana Murthy is wrong

description: The Indian film industry mourns the loss of Manoj Kumar, a legendary actor and filmmaker who passed away on 4 April 2025. A state funeral was held, with many Bollywood stars paying their last respects. A prayer meeting organized by CINTAA honored the veteran star, with notable figures from the industry attending to remember his contributions and lasting legacy.
title: Manoj Kumar’s prayer meet: Celebrities arrive to pay tribute

description: Virat Kohli delighted fans by dancing to John Cena’s theme song in a viral video alongside Tim David. Kohli discussed his strong bond with Rohit Sharma, emphasizing their mutual trust and collaboration, crucial in many of their match-winning performances for India. Up next, RCB face Mumbai Indians in a much-anticipated clash on Monday.
title: Virat Kohli imitates John Cena - WATCH

description: Pope Francis, 88, made his first public appearance at the Vatican since his recent hospital discharge for pneumonia treatment, attending a Jubilee Mass for the sick. In a message, he thanked healthcare workers and emphasized the importance of God's care for those who suffer.
title: Watch: Pope Francis makes surprise appearance in Vatican square

description: Delhi Capitals' mentor Kevin Pietersen has taken a short break to the Maldives, missing their next game against RCB. The Axar Patel-led team remains undefeated in IPL 2025, with key contributions from Mitchell Starc, Kuldeep Yadav, and KL Rahul, positioning them as strong title contenders.

description: In an IPL 2025 clash, Dhoni’s keen instincts were showcased when he silently indicated a dismissal call from the dressing room, moments before the umpire's decision. Despite Dhoni's sharp judgment, Delhi Capitals secured a 25-run victory against Chennai Super Kings, extending their winning streak. But what truly caught the fans’ attention was Dhoni, calmly sitting in the dressing room, mouthing the words “out hai” even before the replay confirmed it — once again showcasing the unmatched cricketing mind of ‘Captain Cool’.
title: MS Dhoni's 'out hai' moment from dressing room goes viral - WATCH

description: Prime Minister Modi refuted Chief Minister Stalin's claim of fund neglect, stating the central government allocated triple the funds for Tamil Nadu's development compared to the prior decade. Despite Stalin's assertions, Modi highlighted substantial financial and infrastructure investment in the state.
title: 'Some people have habit of crying': PM's veiled jab at CM Stalin over funds
Stalin skips PM's event in TN, demands 'promise' over fair delimitation

description: Phoebe Gates, daughter of Microsoft founder Bill Gates, is launching a podcast called "The Burnouts" and a fashion website named "Phia." She aims to establish her own identity in the sustainable fashion industry despite concerns of being seen as a 'Nepo Baby.'
title: Bill Gates’ daughter Phoebe reveals parents' advice after launching fashion website

description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai has praised Meta's AI team for launching the Llama 4 models, which boast advanced capabilities in reasoning and efficiency. Meta's Scout and Maverick models compete with leading AI models from Google and OpenAI, with Behemoth in development. Previously, Pichai commended Elon Musk for the Grok-3 AI model introduction.
title: Google CEO Sundar Pichai congratulates Facebook AI team: ‘Never a dull …’

description: JK Rowling criticized Russell Brand after he defended Andrew Tate on social media. Both Brand and Tate face serious sexual assault allegations. Brand is set to appear in court, while Tate faces legal battles in the US and Romania on charges including human trafficking and abuse.
title: JK Rowling slams Russell Brand for siding with fellow sexual abuser Andrew Tate

description: The Karnataka Examinations Authority (KEA) has released the KCET 2025 admit card on its official website. Registered candidates can download it by logging in with their credentials. They must verify all details and follow exam-day instructions mentioned on the admit card. KCET 2025 will be held on April 15, 16, and 17 in two shifts across the state.
title: KCET 2025 admit card released: Check direct link to download hall ticket and other details here
Sudarsan Pattnaik becomes first Indian to win UK’s Fred Darrington Sand Master Award

description: Massive 'Hands Off' protests were held in over 1,200 locations worldwide, targeting President Trump's policies and Elon Musk's political influence. Demonstrations in cities like New York, London, and Washington DC expressed concerns over tariffs, immigration raids, and social spending cuts.
title: 'Tax the rich, not penguins': Slogans at ‘Hands Off!’ protests target Trump, Musk

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi inaugurated the new Pamban rail bridge in Tamil Nadu, reconnecting the mainland to Rameswaram Island. The advanced vertical lift bridge, costing around Rs 550 crore, replaces the old structure and supports higher train speeds, enhancing railway and maritime connectivity.
title: PM Modi inaugurates new Pamban rail bridge - check schedule, key features

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi shared an aerial video of Ram Setu on Ram Navami, which he described as a 'divine coincidence' that coincided with his virtual viewing of the Surya Tilak ceremony in Ayodhya. While in Sri Lanka, Modi visited the Jaya Sri Maha Bodhi temple in Anuradhapura and launched several projects with President Anura Kumara Dissanayake.
title: PM Modi’s Ram Setu darshan happens as Surya Tilak ceremony takes place in Ayodhya

description: Chennai Super Kings faced their third consecutive loss in IPL 2025 against Delhi Capitals, falling short by 25 runs. Despite the defeat, a viral image of young wicketkeeper-batter Vansh Bedi calmly napping amidst the tension provided comic relief for fans. DC now leads the standings, while CSK drops to ninth place after four games.
title: Vansh Bedi's nap in CSK dugout steals the spotlight in viral image

description: Nawab Sheikh, a 27-year-old from Domkal, created a mobile bed on wheels that became an internet sensation. However, police seized the vehicle for violating Motor Vehicles Act rules. Nawab spent over a year and Rs 2.15 lakh on the project, funded by selling his wife's jewellery. Despite initial fame, Nawab faced copyright issues and his Facebook account was blocked.
title: Viral video: Man sells wife’s jewellery to build 'bed cart' but police seize it

description: The White House posted a video showing immigrants in shackles boarding a deportation flight, with a cheerful song in the background, prompting strong criticism for dehumanizing immigrants. Last month, a similar video with another song caused backlash, and the band involved criticized the unauthorized use and misinterpretation of their music.
title: White House’s deportation video with 'Na Na Hey Hey' song triggers backlash

description: Anti-Elon Musk sentiment is growing in the UK and Europe, with activist groups using satire and public art to critique Musk's controversial political ties. These protests aim to impact Tesla's brand and stock, highlighting Musk's support for far-right causes and misinformation.
title: 'Goes from 0 to 1939 in 3 seconds': Tesla 'swasticar' satire targets Musk in London

description: D Gukesh, the world chess champion, struggled in the 2025 Freestyle Chess Grand Slam Tour's opening leg but remains optimistic for the Paris leg. Despite a challenging format, Gukesh aims to improve. The Paris event, featuring strong competitors like Hikaru Nakamura, promises a thrilling contest and a chance for Gukesh to redeem himself.
title: 'Gukesh accepted he didn't do well'

description: Kunal Kamra seeks clarity from BookMyShow on listing his shows after being removed from its roster. His delisting followed controversy over his remarks about Eknath Shinde. Kamra also critiqued Bhavish Aggarwal, Sudha Murthy, and Anand Mahindra during a recent performance in Mumbai, sparking reactions from the audience.
title: Kunal Kamra sends a 'Please ...' message to Bookmyshow after it 'removes him'

description: Max Verstappen won the 2025 Japanese Grand Prix, overcoming early technical problems and late pressure from Lando Norris. Verstappen maintained his lead despite gear issues and a slow pit stop. Norris' late attempts to overtake were unsuccessful. The race featured strategic moves by McLaren and Red Bull, with Verstappen's victory ending his winless start to the season.
title: Max Verstappen wins Japanese Grand Prix 2025, his first victory of the season
Delhi woman’s ride with female driver turns into unforgettable experience

description: A villager offered water to a cheetah family in Kuno National Park, showing a shift in human-animal dynamics after previous hostility. However, forest officers are concerned about human-wildlife interaction. The incident has led to the suspension of the villager involved.
title: Forest department driver offers water to thirsty cheetahs, suspended
‘Hands Off!’ protests in US: What sparked them & why people are taking to streets

description: Virat Kohli, ahead of the IPL 2025 match between RCB and MI, spoke about his long-standing bond with Rohit Sharma, highlighting their trust and shared insights. While RCB are in a strong position, MI have struggled, making their upcoming game crucial. Kohli expressed gratitude for their shared journey and the memories created with Team India.
title: 'Happy for all the memories': Virat reflects on deep bond with Rohit

description: Jacqueline Fernandez’s mother, Kim, has passed away after being hospitalized in critical condition. The actress was seen frequently at Mumbai’s Lilavati Hospital, staying by her mother’s side. Kim had previously suffered health issues. Jacqueline missed her IPL opening performance to prioritize her family during this difficult time.
title: Jacqueline Fernandez's mother Kim, passes away following health complications
PM Modi, SL president unveil India-assisted railway projects in Anuradhapura
Spain: Tens of thousands protest nationwide housing crisis

description: Canada's Parliament was placed under lockdown after a man barricaded himself inside the East Block on Parliament Hill. Ottawa Police and heavily armed officers cordoned off the area, which houses senators and their staff. An emergency alert urged individuals to seek shelter. No injuries were reported, but the lockdown remained as a precautionary measure.
title: Canadian parliament under lockdown after man barricades himself inside
Anant Ambani completes 170-km padyatra from Jamnagar to Dwarkadhish Temple

description: Star pacer Jasprit Bumrah has rejoined Mumbai Indians, bringing excitement to fans ahead of crucial matches in IPL 2025. After a rehab period, his return strengthens MI’s bowling attack and offers leadership. Skipper Hardik Pandya hinted at Bumrah’s comeback, now confirmed. Bumrah’s lethal skills and composure will be pivotal as MI look to improve their standings this season.
title: 'Ready to Roar': Jasprit Bumrah joins Mumbai Indians squad

description: Transgender student Marcy Rheintgen's arrest for using a women's restroom in Florida is seen as a challenge to new restrictive laws. Her act of civil disobedience, aimed at highlighting the laws' absurdity, has drawn significant attention from civil rights groups. Legal experts view this as a potential landmark case for transgender rights in the US.
title: Trans college student arrested in Florida Capitol for defying bathroom law

description: Protests erupted across the US as thousands of demonstrators voiced opposition to President Trump and adviser Elon Musk. The administration faces backlash for budget cuts to public services and rollbacks on LGBTQ+ protections. Critics accuse it of dismantling democracy. The rallies included civil rights groups, labor unions, and other community organizations.
title: After Turkey, Pikachu spotted at anti-Trump rally in US

description: Anant Ambani, director of Reliance Industries, completed a 140-km padyatra in Gujarat to mark his 30th birthday. Despite chronic health issues, his journey from Jamnagar to Dwarkadhish Temple included daily walks of 12 to 15 km, visits to temples, and expressions of gratitude for spiritual support.
title: Anant Ambani completes 170-km padyatra from Jamnagar to Dwarkadhish Temple

description: Tensions between the US and Iran increased after an Iranian newspaper called for the assassination of President Trump. The article came days after Trump warned of military strikes if Iran did not cooperate on its nuclear program. The newspaper, linked to Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei, has repeatedly advocated for Trump’s assassination.
title: 'Bullets into that empty skull': Khamenei’s mouthpiece calls for Trump’s death

description: Two British Labour MPs, Yuan Yang and Abtisam Mohamed, were detained and denied entry by Israeli authorities, who accused them of anti-Israel rhetoric and intending to document security activities. This incident has caused a diplomatic dispute, with UK foreign secretary David Lammy expressing strong disapproval of their treatment.
title: Israel detains two UK Labour MPs over alleged plan to 'spread hate'

description: Microsoft celebrates its 50th anniversary, with co-founder Bill Gates reflecting on political naivety during the company's early days. Gates admits underestimating government relations and misjudging the value of diverse team-building skills. Despite setbacks, Microsoft evolved into a tech giant under successive leadership.
title: Microsoft founder Bill Gates shares the 'political mistake' he made

description: A $600,000 federal grant to Southern University for researching sustainable feminine hygiene products was revoked due to misinformation. The mistaken narrative, pushed by the Department of Government Efficiency, led to backlash and safety concerns, although the project briefly mentioned transgender men in its context.
title: Musk's ​Doge mislabels feminine hygiene study as transgender, cancels $600,000 grant

description: Sanju Samson became Rajasthan Royals’ most successful captain with a 50-run win over Punjab Kings, surpassing Shane Warne's 31 wins. The victory marked his 32nd win as skipper. Yashasvi Jaiswal and Jofra Archer excelled, contributing to RR's commanding performance. The win also ended Punjab Kings captain Shreyas Iyer’s eight-match unbeaten run.
title: Sanju Samson becomes most successful RR captain in IPL history

description: A 43-year-old man, Krishnappa, fatally stabbed his wife in Chikkathoguru, Electronics City, over suspicions of infidelity. The incident occurred at 8pm when K Sharada was returning home from work. Krishnappa, who had planned the attack, was quickly apprehended by bystanders and handed over to the police.

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad face Gujarat Titans in a crucial IPL match at Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium. SRH aim to end a three-match losing streak but struggles with inconsistent batting and bowling. In contrast, GT, with strong batting and disciplined bowling, seem to have an edge. The pitch favours batting first, with high totals predicted.
title: IPL match today: SRH vs GT in Hyderabad - all you need to know

description: Salman Khan's action drama Sikandar concluded its first week at the domestic box office with earnings of approximately ₹97.50 crore. Despite a strong opening and a strategic Eid release, the film witnessed a steady decline, casting doubts on its potential to surpass the ₹100 crore mark within the initial week.
title: Sikandar day 7: Salman Khan's film falls short of Rs 100 crore at end of week 1

description: The United States has revoked all visas held by South Sudanese passport holders in response to South Sudan's refusal to accept deported citizens. The visa actions come amid rising tensions and political instability within South Sudan, exacerbated by internal power struggles and fears of renewed civil conflict.
title: 'Stop taking advantage': US slaps South Sudan with sweeping visa ban

description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy has criticised the US for its weak reaction to Russia's missile strike in Ukraine, which killed 18 people, including nine children, in Kryvyi Rih. Zelenskyy expressed disappointment with US Ambassador Brink's failure to directly name Russia as responsible for the attack in her statement.
title: 'Strong country, weak reaction': Zelenskyy blasts US over Russian missile strike

description: A motorcyclist named Naveen Gupta died in Kanpur after being hit by an Innova during a high-speed race with a BMW. The accident occurred near the South Cricket Academy, resulting in Gupta being thrown into a parked car. The Innova's driver fled but was later arrested.
title: Watch: Innova ‘racing’ with BMW kills biker in Uttar Pradesh

description: Wedbush Securities warns that President Trump's proposed tariffs could cause severe economic damage to the U.S. tech sector. The tariffs may lead to skyrocketing electronics prices, disrupted supply chains, and delayed tech innovation, potentially erasing years of progress and giving China a competitive edge in the AI revolution.
title: Wall Street's analyst calls Trump's tariffs lottery for China, and brutal for...

description: Home Minister Amit Shah urged Maoists in Chhattisgarh's Bastar to lay down arms and join the mainstream, highlighting the government's commitment to development and peace. Shah emphasized the need for infrastructure improvements and assured protection for those who surrender, aiming to eliminate the insurgency by March-April 2026.
title: Amit Shah calls Naxals brothers, says no one cheers their death

description: Fort Bend County Judge K P George, an Indian-American Democrat, was arrested on two felony counts of money laundering related to wire fraud and falsifying a campaign finance report. George, who denies the charges, faces potential prison time and significant political fallout. His earlier indictment concerned fabricated racist attacks during his re-election campaign.
title: Fort Bend’s Indian-American judge indicted for alleged money laundering

description: The Golden State Warriors are reportedly considering signing Russell Westbrook to boost their roster. Westbrook, a 9-time All-Star and former MVP, could offer veteran leadership, playmaking, and bench strength. While his efficiency may not be elite, his energy and experience might be beneficial for the Warriors' title aspirations, contingent on chemistry and financial factors.
title: NBA offseason rumors: Warriors eyeing 2x All-Star to form Big 3 with Curry and Butler

title: Ram Navami: Messages, wishes, and greetings to share on final day of Chaitra Navratri

description: A 24-year-old woman, Priyanka Rawat, died after falling from a rollercoaster in Delhi's Fun N Food Water & Amusement Park due to a seatbelt malfunction. title: 'Faulty seatbelt': Woman falls to death from amusement park ride in Delhi

description: Prime Minister Modi's visit to Sri Lanka led to a tripartite agreement involving the UAE to develop Trincomalee as an energy hub. The project aims to enhance Sri Lanka's energy security and economy. This move counters China's significant investments in the region.
title: Eye on China, India inks SL deal for energy hub in Trincomalee

description: Entrepreneurs in Kathmandu stress the need for political stability to enable consistent business policies and long-term planning. title: For Nepal businesses, most valuable currency's stability

description: Rajasthan forest department allowed a private event inside Ranthambore Fort after sunset, violating NTCA guidelines. Vehicles with loud music systems were involved, raising concerns about tiger conservation. State agriculture minister Kirori Lal Meena protested and requested a probe to hold officials accountable.
title: VIPs party at Ranthambore, shatter tiger zone tranquility
